"a.虚弱的 【英】 adj. 虚弱的(physically weak) 【考】 反义词：hale(强壮的 ) 【记】 in(不)+firm(坚定) →不坚定的 【同】 派生词: infirmity n. (虚弱feebleness; weakness) adj. 衰老体弱的; 意志不坚的; 不坚固的 【记】firm(n 公司adj 结实的; 坚固的); infirmity(n 虚弱; 缺点) 【反】hale(adj 强壮的; 老人矍铄的) 【记】in 不 + firm 结实 infirm (adj.)  late 14c., ""weak, unsound"" (of things), from Latin infirmus ""weak, frail, feeble"" (figuratively ""superstitious, pusillanimous, inconstant""), from in- ""not, opposite of"" (see in- (1)) + firmus (see firm (adj.)). Of persons, ""not strong, unhealthy,"" first recorded c.1600. As a noun from 1711."
